acceptGarden(uint256).details: Use this function to accept a new garden and open it to location. The caller must be the admin contract.

acceptGardenOffer(uint256).details: Use this function to accept a location offer. Caller must be the tenant.

addAccessCodeToGarden(uint256,uint256[2].details: Use this function to add access code to a garden. The caller must be the garden's owner and prove it.

params._encryptedCode: the code encrypted with the tenant's public key
params._hashCode: the hash of the access code
params._proofA: the first part of the proof
params._proofB: the second part of the proof
params._proofC: the third part of the proof

addDispute(uint256).details: Use this function to add a dispute in case of disagreement between owner and tenant.

addGradeToGarden(uint256,int256).details: Tenant should use this function to add a grade to his locations between 1 and 5.

closeDispute(uint256,uint256,uint256).details: Use this function to close a dispute and give back ether amounts to correct people. Must be call by the admin contract.

createGarden(uint256[2],string,uint32,st.details: Use this function to add a new garden.

params._coOwners: in case of multiple owners : all owners' addresses, could be empty
params._multipleOwners: boolean that represents multiple owners for a garden or not
params._secretHash: hash of the user' secret; must be in decimal form int[2]

deleteGardenOffer(uint256,uint256[2],uin.details: Use this function to delete an offer that has not received any response. Ownly the garden's owner could call and only if an offer is running.

params._proofA: the first part of the proof
params._proofB: the second part of the proof
params._proofC: the third part of the proof

getRefundBeforeLocation(uint256).details: Use this function to get refund and to cancel a location only if access code is missing.

proposeGardenOffer(uint256,address,uint2.details: Use this function to propose a new location offer. The caller must be the owner, after agreement with the tenant offchain.

params._proofA: the first part of the proof
params._proofB: the second part of the proof
params._proofC: the third part of the proof

rejectGarden(uint256).details: Use this function to reject a new garden and blacklist it. The caller must be the admin contract.

updateGardenContact(uint256,string).details: Use this function to update the contact of a garden. The caller must be the garden's owner.

params._contact: the new contact of the garden

updateGardenSecretHash(uint256,uint256[2.details: Use this function to update the secret of the secret of a garden. The caller must be the garden's owner and must prove it by sending the preimage of the secret hash.

params._newSecretHash: the new hash of the secret's garden
params._proofA: the first part of the proof
params._proofB: the second part of the proof
params._proofC: the third part of the proof

updateLocationStatusAndGetPayment(uint25.details: Use the function to update location status after location and get payment. The caller must be the garden's owner.

params._proofA: the first part of the proof
params._proofB: the second part of the proof
params._proofC: the third part of the proof
